# .dockerignore — exclude everything by default, opt files into the build
# context explicitly. This stops the build from inheriting host secrets
# (.env, wal directories, *.pem) and keeps image layers small.
#
# Builder stage in deploy/Dockerfile does `COPY . /build/gateway` then
# `pip wheel --no-deps`. pyproject.toml's package-data globs decide which
# files end up in the wheel; everything outside that path is dead weight.
*

# --- What the wheel needs to be built ---
!src/
!pyproject.toml
!README.md
!LICENSE

# --- Build-time files we want to avoid even inside src/ ---
src/**/__pycache__
src/**/*.pyc
src/**/*.pyo
src/gateway/lineage/dashboard/node_modules
src/gateway/lineage/dashboard/.vite

# --- Secrets and runtime state — never bake these into image layers ---
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/gateway-bootstrap-key.txt
**/walacor-wal*
**/*.db
**/*.db-wal
**/*.db-shm
**/*.log
